title: fix warnings about _XOPEN_SOURCE redefinition.
body_html: Every compilation unit whose headers recursively include Python.h need to include Python.h first. This is a known limitation of the Python headers. This patch works around it by adding Python.h in the right places. Also fixes a int->void* cast warning by making the int an int64_t.
